<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7184665>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Oropedium tatamaense sp. nov. A) Frontal view, B) dorsal view, C) lateral view, D) frontolateral view. lc: lateral carinae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7184665/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7184667>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Male abdomen and genitalia of Oropedium tatamaense sp. nov.: Abdomen views: A) Dorsal, B) ventral, C) lateral. Pygofer views: D) ventral, E) lateral. Subgenital plate views: F) ventral, G) dorsolateral. Styles views: H) ventral, I) dorsal, J) lateral. Aedeagus views: K) lateral, L) posterolateral, M) anterolateral, N) caudal. tr: transversal ridge." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7184667/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7184661>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Known record of Oropedium tatamaense sp. nov. The arrow indicates ‘Piedra Bomba’ (3750 masl), the place where specimens were collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7184661/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7184671>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Some important morphological traits in Membracinae. Frontal view: A) Aconophora flavipes (Aconophorini), B) Enchenopa concolor (Membracini), C) Philya sp. (Hypsoprorini), D) Talipes fenestratus (Talipedini), E) Bolbonota sp. (Membracini). F) Alchisme grossa (Hoplophorionini). Lateral view: G) A. flavipes, H) E. concolor, I) Philya sp., J) T. fenestratus. ac: accessory carinae; apl: apical limbus; cl: clavus; fc: frontoclypeus; ha: humeral angles; irr: irregular carinae; lap: lateral apical carina; lc: lateral carina; Rb: vein R bifurcation; sa: supra-antennal ledges; shc: suprahumeral carina; *: extra-crossveins." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7184671/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7184675>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Some important morphological traits in Membracinae. Lateral view: A) Bolbonota sp. (Membracini); B) Alchisme grossa (Hoplophorionini), C) Leioscyta cf. spiralis (Membracini). Lateral view abdomen: D) Bolbonota sp.; E) Notocera crassicornis (Hypsoprorini); F) Cladonota apicalis (Hypsoprorini). mst: mesothoracic tarsus; mtt: metathoracic tarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7184675/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

